115 Then the valley, as the day was spent, 116 from Pratomagno to the great ridge covered itself 117 with mist; and the sky above made itself intent,
118 so that the heavy air turned into water; 119 the rain fell, and to the ditches came 120 of it that which the earth did not suffer;
